  "texts": [
    "In addition, Blattgerste et al (2018) compared eye-tracking-based interaction in VR and AR with head-tracking evaluating the benefits of eye-tracking.",
    "They showed that gaze-tracking outperforms head-tracking in many features such as speed, user preference, and task load.",
    "A wide variety of research articles was reviewed in this work.",
    "To this end, Scopus was used as the principal crosslibrary search tool.",
    "Given the purpose of this survey, the Scopus query was performed by seeking the following terms in the title with the AND operator: \"eye\", \"tracking\", \"gaze\", \"virtual\", \"reality\" and \"vr\"."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In addition, Blattgerste et al (2018) compared eye-tracking-based interaction in VR and AR with head-tracking evaluating the benefits of eye-tracking."
  ]
